In article <1994Mar23.140308.6571@nntp.nta.no>, thor@unik.no (Thor Kristoffersen) writes:> 
> > [independent subkeys]
> Yes, it's possible, but there's not much point in doing it
> since differential cryptanalysis finds the subkeys directly.

Wrong. Independent subkeys complicate diff.cryptan from 2^47
to 2^61... Read the book!

> Using independent subkeys is generally a bad idea, since it
> facilitates various split-and-conquer attacks (like the
> meet-in-the-middle attack, for instance).

Wrong again...

In a nutshell: it's better to generate independent subkeys,
however you won't be compatible with the existing hardware
and software.
